    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lab-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required Gradation level for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 at MRL 2. GCI-controlled discretization error, bench-validated hemolysis predictions within 12% of experimental data, and documented model form justification collectively support the claim that the CFD model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The relative hemolysis index criterion (RH < 1) is met at all operating points. Credibility assessment accepted for regulatory submission.",
